.SH NAME
HTMLLinkElement.imageSizes \- HTMLLinkElement: imageSizes property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]imageSizes\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLLinkElement\f[R] interface indicates the size and conditions
for the preloaded images defined by the \f[CR]imageSrcset\f[R] property.
It reflects the value of the \f[CR]<link>\f[R] element\(cqs
\f[CR]imagesizes\f[R] attribute.
This property can retrieve or set the \f[CR]imagesizes\f[R] attribute
value.
.PP
The \f[CR]<link>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]imagesizes\f[R] attribute is
the same as the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]sizes\f[R]
attribute: a comma\-separated \f[B]source size\f[R] list.
Each source size includes a media condition, the size of the image as a
\f[CR]length\f[R], or the keyword \f[CR]auto\f[R], which must come
first.
For more information about the syntax of the \f[CR]sizes\f[R] attribute,
see \f[CR]<img>\f[R].
.PP
The \f[CR]imagesrcset\f[R] and \f[CR]imagesizes\f[R] attributes are only
relevant on \f[CR]<link>\f[R] elements that have both a \f[CR]rel\f[R]
attribute set to \f[CR]preload\f[R] and the \f[CR]as\f[R] attribute set
to \f[CR]image\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A string composed of comma\-separated source sizes, or the empty string
\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R] if unspecified.
.SH EXAMPLES
Given the following \f[CR]<link>\f[R] element:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]link\f[R]
  rel=\(dqpreload\(dq
  as=\(dqimage\(dq
  imagesrcset=\(dqnarrow.png, medium.png 600w, wide.png 1200w\(dq
  imagesizes=\(dq(max\-width: 400px) 200px, (width \f[B]<\f[R] 600px) 75vw, 50vw\(dq />
.EE
.PP
\&...we can retrieve and update the \f[CR]imagesizes\f[R] attribute
value with the \f[CR]imageSizes\f[R] property:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] link = document.querySelector(\(dqlink\(dq);
log(\(gaOriginal: ${link.imageSizes}\(ga);

\f[I]// Change the value\f[R]
link.imageSizes = \(dq50vw\(dq;
log(\(gaUpdated: ${link.imageSizes}\(ga);
.EE
